    <summary>WireGuard tunnel manager for non-admin Windows users via a privileged background service.</summary>
    <description>## WireGuard Manager

WireGuard for Windows only allows non-admin users to activate and deactivate existing tunnels (via `LimitedOperatorUI`). All other operations — creating, importing, editing or deleting tunnels — still require full administrator rights.

**WireGuard Manager** solves this through a two-layer architecture:

- A **Windows service** running as `LocalSystem` that manages tunnels.
- A **desktop UI** (no privileges required) that communicates with the service over a secure local Named Pipe.

Users can view, connect, disconnect, create, import, edit and delete tunnels **without UAC or admin rights**, controlled by a role system backed by Windows local groups.

### Features

- Real-time tunnel status (connected / disconnected / pending / error)
- Connect, disconnect and restart tunnels
- Create, import, edit and delete WireGuard `.conf` configurations
- Per-tunnel auto-start
- Tunnel statistics: local IP, endpoint, last handshake, Rx/Tx, uptime
- Public IP detection with 7-provider fallback chain
- Windows Toast notifications on connect/disconnect
- Tray icon reflecting tunnel state
- Full audit log at `%ProgramData%\WireGuard-WinUserUI\audit.jsonl`
- RBAC via Windows local groups (Viewer / Operator / Advanced Operator / Admin)

### Requirements

- Windows 10 (build 17763) or Windows 11
- [WireGuard for Windows](https://community.chocolatey.org/packages/wireguard) must be installed
- .NET 8 Runtime (bundled in the MSI installer)
    </description>
